text: The Arizona Legislature is the Legislative branch of the Government of Arizona. It is Bicameral, with the Upper house being the Arizona Senate and the Lower house being the Arizona House of Representatives. There are 30 legislative districts, which each elect one senator and two representatives. https://www.ncsl.org/elections-and-campaigns/eligibility-requirements-to-run- for-the-state-legislature ==References== Category:Arizona Legislature
